I am trying to migrate some code from WPILib 2023 to WPILib 2024, and it seems that the the JSON parsing code I was previously using will no longer compile.

It’s a call to wpi::json::parse() when passing in a wpi::raw_fd_istream. The error log is as follows:

include/wpi/json.h:4037:37: error: no matching function for call to 'input_adapter(wpi::raw_fd_istream&)'
 4037 |         parser(detail::input_adapter(std::forward<InputType>(i)), cb, allow_exceptions, ignore_comments).parse(true, result);
      |                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

The templating here goes pretty deep so I didn’t spend much time digging around. My question is if this is unintentional or if there is a new, better way to parse JSON?

Thanks!
